{
  include "backend/registries/llm_config.hocon"

  "metadata": {
    "description": "Agentic wireless AP reboot orchestration using safety guardrails, dry-run execution, validation, and reporting.",
    "tags": ["wireless", "operations", "ap-reboot", "hackathon"],
    "sample_queries": [
      "Find APs that are safe to reboot for site tag BLR-CAMPUS. Use uptime greater than 100 days, zero clients only, dry-run mode, and generate the validation report."
    ]
  },

  "instructions_prefix": """
  You are part of a wireless operations agent network. Only handle AP reboot planning, safety checks, validation, and reporting. Do not reveal or request credentials. Do not use real client data. Prefer dry-run mode unless explicit live approval is present.
  """,

  "aaosa_instructions": """
  When you receive an inquiry:
  1. Decide which specialist agent should handle each part of the request.
  2. Ask the specialist agents for their required inputs.
  3. Delegate the work to the proper specialist agents.
  4. Compile their responses into one clear wireless-operations answer.
  5. Clearly state eligible APs, blocked APs, safety reasons, dry-run actions, and validation results.
  """,

  "tools": [
    {
      "name": "Wireless_Reboot_Copilot",
      "function": {
        "description": "Coordinates safe AP reboot planning using inventory, eligibility, risk, execution, validation, and reporting agents."
      },
      "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
      You are the front agent for the AP reboot workflow. Your job is to understand the user's maintenance request, delegate to the specialist agents, and return a concise final answer with safety explanations.
      Always use dry-run mode unless the user explicitly provides live approval and a maintenance window.
      """ ${aaosa_instructions},
      "tools": ["Inventory_Agent", "Eligibility_Agent", "Risk_Agent", "Execution_Agent", "Validation_Agent", "Report_Agent"]
    },

    {
      "name": "Inventory_Agent",
      "function": {
        "description": "Reviews AP inventory and identifies APs by site tag, controller, uptime, client count, and joined state.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "site_tag": {"type": "string", "description": "Site tag to review"},
            "inventory_path": {"type": "string", "description": "Path to the AP inventory CSV"}
          }
        }
      },
      "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
      Review inventory inputs and call APRebootTool to load and summarize candidate APs. Focus on site tag, uptime, client count, reachability, and controller state.
      """,
      "command": "Call APRebootTool with action full_report, inventory_path, and site_tag.",
      "tools": ["APRebootTool"]
    },

    {
      "name": "Eligibility_Agent",
      "function": {
        "description": "Selects APs that meet uptime and zero-client eligibility rules.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "site_tag": {"type": "string"},
            "min_uptime_days": {"type": "integer"}
          }
        }
      },
      "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
      Select only APs with uptime greater than or equal to the requested threshold and zero active clients. Do not approve APs with active clients.
      """,
      "command": "Call APRebootTool and return eligible_aps plus any blocked_aps.",
      "tools": ["APRebootTool"]
    },

    {
      "name": "Risk_Agent",
      "function": {
        "description": "Applies risk guardrails before reboot planning.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "site_tag": {"type": "string"},
            "min_uptime_days": {"type": "integer"}
          }
        }
      },
      "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
      Block APs that are unreachable, not joined, outside maintenance window, critical site APs, below uptime threshold, or have active clients. Always explain the blocker reason.
      """,
      "command": "Call APRebootTool and return blocked_aps with reasons.",
      "tools": ["APRebootTool"]
    },

    {
      "name": "Execution_Agent",
      "function": {
        "description": "Builds reboot batches and performs dry-run or approved reboot execution.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "site_tag": {"type": "string"},
            "dry_run": {"type": "boolean"}
          }
        }
      },
      "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
      Default to dry-run mode. If live mode is requested without explicit approval, refuse live execution and provide a dry-run plan instead.
      """,
      "command": "Call APRebootTool and return reboot_plan and reboot_results.",
      "tools": ["APRebootTool"]
    },

    {
      "name": "Validation_Agent",
      "function": {
        "description": "Validates AP recovery after reboot actions.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "site_tag": {"type": "string"},
            "dry_run": {"type": "boolean"}
          }
        }
      },
      "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
      Validate whether APs are joined and reachable after reboot. In dry-run mode, clearly state that no live validation was performed.
      """,
      "command": "Call APRebootTool and return validation.",
      "tools": ["APRebootTool"]
    },

    {
      "name": "Report_Agent",
      "function": {
        "description": "Creates the final AP reboot orchestration report.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "site_tag": {"type": "string"},
            "min_uptime_days": {"type": "integer"},
            "dry_run": {"type": "boolean"}
          }
        }
      },
      "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
      Produce a clean final report that includes selected APs, blocked APs, reboot actions, validation, and safety notes.
      """,
      "command": "Call APRebootTool with action report.",
      "tools": ["APRebootTool"]
    },

    {
      "name": "APRebootTool",
      "function": {
        "description": "Python coded tool for AP reboot candidate selection, safety checks, dry-run execution, validation, and report generation.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "action": {"type": "string", "description": "full_report or report"},
            "inventory_path": {"type": "string", "description": "Path to AP inventory CSV"},
            "site_tag": {"type": "string", "description": "Site tag filter"},
            "min_uptime_days": {"type": "integer", "description": "Minimum AP uptime days"},
            "batch_size": {"type": "integer", "description": "Maximum AP count per reboot batch"},
            "dry_run": {"type": "boolean", "description": "Use dry-run mode"}
          },
          "required": ["action"]
        }
      },
      "class": "coded_tools.ap_reboot.ap_reboot_tool.APRebootTool"
    }
  ]
}
